        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 28 at 11:01AM EST by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>HAZARDS...An area of moderate snow and thick haze which can rapidly
reduce visibility to less than a quarter of a mile. Latest highway
cameras also indicate snow beginning to accumulate on the roadways,
bringing slippery to potentially hazardous road conditions.

LOCATION AND MOVEMENT...At 1059 AM EST, an area of heavy snow was
near Saxtons River, or 8 miles north of Townshend moving east at 45
MPH.

THIS AREA OF HEAVY SNOW WILL BE NEAR...
Bellows Falls and Saxtons River around 1105 AM EST.

SAFETY INFO...
Conditions can deteriorate rapidly in winter weather situations. Be
prepared for snow or ice covered roads. Slow down and allow extra
time to reach your destination.
</description>
